loaf /ləʊf/

(loafing,loafed,loafs,loaves) 

1. N-COUNT A loaf of bread is bread which has been shaped and baked in one piece. It is usually large enough for more than one person and can be cut into slices. (一) 条 (面包) 

例： ...a loaf of crusty bread. …一条硬皮面包。 

2. V-I If you loaf , you spend time in a lazy way, doing nothing in particular, especially when you should be working. 闲着 

例： There were always a lot of men loafing in the shop. 总有许多人在商店里闲逛。

